The terror-accused Thulsie twins’ case returns to court today. They have been behind bars for over 5-and-a-half years and have still not stood trial. eNCA's Heidi Giokos has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Thulsie twins - accused of terrorism - are expected back in the High Court in Johannesburg on Monday. Tony-Lee and Brandon-Lee Thulsie were arrested in 2016 following raids in various parts of Gauteng. READ: Thulsie twins back in Joburg court They are accused of being part of a Jihadist group and plotting to blow-up buildings in Johannesburg. They have been in custody since their arrest in 2016.